{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"name":"ir","display_name":"R","language":"R"},"language_info":{"mimetype":"text/x-r-source","name":"R","pygments_lexer":"r","version":"3.6.0","file_extension":".r","codemirror_mode":"r"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[{"sourceType":"datasetVersion","sourceId":14882018,"datasetId":9521443,"databundleVersionId":15745150}],"isInternetEnabled":false,"language":"r","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"source":"<a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/code/joylorna/omnisphere-global-retail-profitability-deep-dive?scriptVersionId=302794801\" target=\"_blank\"><img align=\"left\" alt=\"Kaggle\" title=\"Open in Kaggle\" src=\"https://kaggle.com/static/images/open-in-kaggle.svg\"></a>","metadata":{},"cell_type":"markdown"},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**OmniSphere Global 2025: Unlocking Retail Profitability — Drivers, Leaks, High-Value Customers & Margin Strategies**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Introduction**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Welcome to the *OmniSphere Global 2025 Performance Review*, a full end-to-end analysis of multinational retail sales data from fiscal year 2025. OmniSphere Global is a diversified mass-market retailer operating 18 stores across six major economies: the US, UK, Canada, China, India, and Nigeria.\n\nDespite stable top-line revenue, leadership sought to uncover the organization's \"Profitability DNA\": Where does revenue translate into sustainable profit—and where does it leak away? This notebook documents a complete analytical pipeline to answer this central question, plus key business drivers like:\n\n* Where are profit margins highest and lowest across regions, categories, and stores?\n* Are low margins driven by high costs or aggressive discounting?\n* Which products are \"heroes\" (high-profit standouts) versus \"inventory anchors\" (high-volume but low/negative profit)?\n* Which customer segments and sales reps deliver the most profitable transactions—and who needs intervention?\n\n*Why this matters*: These insights guide inventory allocation, pricing policies, commission structures, promotional controls, and targeted marketing—shifting focus from revenue growth to net profit maximization in competitive global markets.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Data Description**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"*Source & Scope*\nSix raw Excel files (one per country), consolidated into a single analytics table via SQL (BigQuery) using UNION ALL. Covers ~3,000 transactions across 18 stores in six markets: United States, United Kingdom, Canada, China, India, and Nigeria. Synthetic retail data representing 2025 sales.\n\n*Key Variables*\n* Identifiers: Transaction ID (tx_id), Date (tx_date), Store Location, Sales Rep, Customer ID\n* Product: Category, Name, ID, Quantity Purchased\n* Pricing: Cost Price, Price per Unit, Discount % (discount_applied)\n* Customer: Age Group, Gender\n\n*Derived Fields*:\n* Total Amount (Revenue): (price_per_unit−discount_applied)×quantity_purchased\n* Profit: (price_per_unit−discount_applied−cost_price)×quantity_purchased\nAll financial metrics rounded to 2 decimal places for accuracy.\n\n*Preprocessing Steps*\n* Standardized column headers, data types (datetime, numeric, currency), and categories (e.g., fixed typos like 'again' → 'sports').\n* Removed duplicates; resolved nulls and flagged suspicious rows (e.g., negative profits, discounts >100%, zero/NULL cost price).\n* Created retail_sales_cleaned analysis view for reproducible workflows (preserves raw data).\n\nThis clean dataset enables robust profitability analysis.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Methodology**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"*Platforms & Tools*\n* Notebook: Kaggle & Github (for reproducibility and presentation).\n* Data Warehouse/SQL: Google BigQuery (aggregation, diagnostics).\n* Visualization: Power BI (dashboards, scorecards, geo-maps, waterfall charts, KPI tables with negative-profit alerts).\n\n*Structured Data-to-Decision Pipeline*\n1. Data Cleaning & Engineering (Excel + BigQuery SQL):\n* Deduplication, type validation, fix inconsistencies/nulls/outliers; keep raw data immutable.\n* UNION ALL merge of six regional tables into retail_sales_cleaned view.\n* Feature engineering: Total Amount, Profit, Customer Persona (age + gender), Discount Intensity.\n\n2. Descriptive & Comparative Analysis (SQL):\n* EDA: Outliers, global averages by country, category, store, sales rep, demographics.\n* Compute margins, totals, baseline margin (no discounts) vs. actual, discount impact (% of potential revenue).\n\n3. Diagnostic & Segmentation Analysis:\n* Demographic: Customer Personas for targeted insights.\n* Sales Force Audit: Rep performance via discount intensity and negative-profit flags.\n* Operational: Flag underperformers (e.g., profit/margin < average or high negative transactions).\n* Use volume-weighted metrics for accurate influence of high-volume data.\n\n4. Visualization & Storytelling (Power BI):\n* Scorecards (Revenue, Profit, Margin), geo-maps (country/store drill-downs), waterfall charts (discount impact), scatter plots, bar charts.\n* Executive dashboard for actionable insights.\n\n*Rationale*\n\nSQL handles scalable, auditable heavy lifting; Power BI delivers accessible visuals for stakeholders. Diagnostics distinguish cost issues (high cost/low baseline margin) from pricing/promotion erosion (high discounts), prioritizing volume-weighted results for real-world impact.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Analysis and Results**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"*Global Financials*\n* Total Revenue (2025): $4.14M\n\n* Total Profit (2025): $959K\n* Global Average Margin: 23.2% (healthy for mass-market retail; variance across countries only 1.3 points)\n\n*Strategic Findings*\n* The Profit King: The United States emerged as the most profitable region ($166,544.53) with the highest profit margin (23.89%).\n\n* Efficiency vs. Volume: While Home & Kitchen drives the highest volume (2,911 units), Electronics is our most efficient category, boasting a $60.59 profit per unit.\n* Discount Discipline: Globally, OmniSphere maintains a very tight discount range of 1.72% – 1.91%, indicating high pricing integrity.\n\nThese insights reveal profit drivers (efficiency in Electronics/US) vs. leaks (discount abuse), guiding pricing, inventory, and rep interventions.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Challenges and Limitations**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"* Missing Variables: No shipping/freight costs (profit = gross margin only); lacks POS/refund logs, biasing negative-profit rows toward discounts/refunds. Future: Add for net profit view.\n* Currency & Comparability: Assumed USD normalization; FX inconsistencies could skew cross-country results—recommend explicit conversions.\n* Sample & Bias: ~3,000 transactions rich but not exhaustive; small-store samples create noisy per-tx metrics (mitigation: min transaction thresholds, outlier flags).\n* Anomalies: Negative profits likely from refunds/unauthorized discounts; manual reconciliation needed for accuracy.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Conclusion**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"OmniSphere Global thrived in 2025 as a healthy, margin-disciplined retailer with strong pricing power: no loss-leading categories (all profitable), discounts tightly controlled (<2%), and consistent global margins (~23%).\n\n*Key Takeaways*\n\n* Profit Drivers: US leads; Electronics excels ($60.59/unit); Young Males/Females are top segments (high profit/order value).\n* Leak Sources: Unauthorized discounts (16–19% by flagged reps) erode margins—distinguish from cost issues via diagnostics.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Code Snipets**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"-- Merge the six tables and create merged table\nCREATE TABLE `project-f57ec015-00f5-4842-84d.omnisphere_retail_sales.retail_sales` AS\nSELECT *\nFROM `project-f57ec015-00f5-4842-84d.omnisphere_retail_sales.sales_canada`\nUNION ALL\nSELECT *\nFROM `project-f57ec015-00f5-4842-84d.omnisphere_retail_sales.sales_china`\nUNION ALL\nSELECT *\nFROM `project-f57ec015-00f5-4842-84d.omnisphere_retail_sales.sales_india`\nUNION ALL\nSELECT *\nFROM `project-f57ec015-00f5-4842-84d.omnisphere_retail_sales.sales_nigeria`\nUNION ALL\nSELECT *\nFROM `project-f57ec015-00f5-4842-84d.omnisphere_retail_sales.sales_uk`\nUNION ALL\nSELECT *\nFROM `project-f57ec015-00f5-4842-84d.omnisphere_retail_sales.sales_us`;\n","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"-- Create total amount column\nALTER TABLE `project-f57ec015-00f5-4842-84d.omnisphere_retail_sales.retail_sales`\nADD COLUMN Total_Amount FLOAT64;\n\n\nUPDATE `project-f57ec015-00f5-4842-84d.omnisphere_retail_sales.retail_sales`\nSET Total_Amount = (Price_per_Unit * Quantity_Purchased) - Discount_Applied\nWHERE TRUE;\n\n\n-- Create Profit column\nALTER TABLE `project-f57ec015-00f5-4842-84d.omnisphere_retail_sales.retail_sales`\nADD COLUMN Profit FLOAT64;\n\n\nUPDATE `project-f57ec015-00f5-4842-84d.omnisphere_retail_sales.retail_sales`\nSET Profit = Total_Amount - (Cost_Price * Quantity_Purchased)\nWHERE TRUE;","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"-- Where is the money actually staying?\n-- total profit per country\nSELECT\nCountry,\n ROUND (SUM(Profit), 2) AS Total_Profit\nFROM `project-f57ec015-00f5-4842-84d.omnisphere_retail_sales.retail_sales`\nGROUP BY Country\nORDER BY Total_Profit DESC;\n\n\n-- profit margin percentage per country\nSELECT\nCountry,\n ROUND((SUM(Profit) / SUM(Total_Amount)) * 100, 2) AS Profit_Margin_Percentage\nFROM `project-f57ec015-00f5-4842-84d.omnisphere_retail_sales.retail_sales`\nGROUP BY Country\nORDER BY Profit_Margin_Percentage DESC;\n\n\n-- cost vs discount\nSELECT\n    Country,\n-- Total Revenue & Profit\n    ROUND(SUM(Total_Amount), 2) AS total_revenue,\n    ROUND(SUM(Profit), 2) AS total_profit,\n-- Actual Profit Margin\n    ROUND(SAFE_DIVIDE(SUM(Profit), SUM(Total_Amount)) * 100, 2)\n        AS actual_profit_margin_pct,\n-- Baseline Margin (No Discounts Applied)\n    ROUND(\n        SAFE_DIVIDE(\n            SUM((Price_per_Unit - Cost_Price) * Quantity_Purchased),\n            SUM(Price_per_Unit * Quantity_Purchased)\n        ) * 100,\n    2) AS baseline_margin_pct,\n-- Discount Impact (% of Revenue Lost to Discounts)\n    ROUND(\n        SAFE_DIVIDE(\n            SUM(Discount_Applied),\n            SUM(Price_per_Unit * Quantity_Purchased)\n        ) * 100,\n    2) AS discount_pct,\n-- Profit Lost Due to Discounts (Absolute Value)\n    ROUND(SUM((Price_per_Unit - Cost_Price) * Quantity_Purchased)\n        - SUM(Profit), 2) AS discount_profit_impact\nFROM `project-f57ec015-00f5-4842-84d.omnisphere_retail_sales.retail_sales`\nGROUP BY Country\nORDER BY actual_profit_margin_pct ASC;","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"-- Who is our most valuable customer?\n-- sales trends in age group and gender\nSELECT\n    CONCAT(Customer_Age_Group, ' ', Customer_Gender) AS Customer_Segment,\n    COUNT(Transaction_ID) AS Total_Transactions,\n    SUM(Quantity_Purchased) AS Total_Units_Sold,\n    ROUND(SUM(Total_Amount), 2) AS Total_Revenue,\n    ROUND(SUM(Profit), 2) AS Total_Profit,\n    -- Average order value helps see who spends the most per visit\n    ROUND(SAFE_DIVIDE(SUM(Total_Amount), COUNT(Transaction_ID)), 2) AS Avg_Transaction_Value\nFROM `project-f57ec015-00f5-4842-84d.omnisphere_retail_sales.retail_sales`\nGROUP BY 1\nORDER BY Total_Profit DESC;\n\n\n-- Which demographic segments generate the highest total profit?\nSELECT\n    CONCAT(Customer_Age_Group, ' ', Customer_Gender) AS Customer_Segment,\n    ROUND(SUM(Profit), 2) AS Total_Profit,\n    ROUND(SUM(Total_Amount), 2) AS Total_Revenue,\n    -- Profit Margin shows the efficiency of the segment\n    ROUND(SAFE_DIVIDE(SUM(Profit), SUM(Total_Amount)) * 100, 2) AS Profit_Margin_Pct,\n    COUNT(Transaction_ID) AS Transaction_Count\nFROM `project-f57ec015-00f5-4842-84d.omnisphere_retail_sales.retail_sales`\nGROUP BY 1\nORDER BY Total_Profit DESC;\n\n\n-- Which groups respond most strongly to discounts?\nSELECT\n    CONCAT(Customer_Age_Group, ' ', Customer_Gender) AS Customer_Segment,\n    ROUND(AVG(SAFE_DIVIDE(Discount_Applied, (Price_per_Unit * Quantity_Purchased))) * 100, 2) AS Avg_Discount_Intensity_Pct,\n    SUM(Quantity_Purchased) AS Total_Units_Bought,\n    ROUND(SUM(Profit), 2) AS Total_Profit\nFROM `project-f57ec015-00f5-4842-84d.omnisphere_retail_sales.retail_sales`\nGROUP BY 1\nORDER BY Avg_Discount_Intensity_Pct DESC;\n\n\n-- Do purchasing patterns differ across countries?\nSELECT\n    Country,\n    COUNT(Transaction_ID) AS Total_Transactions,\n    ROUND(AVG(Total_Amount), 2) AS Avg_Order_Value,\n    ROUND(AVG(Quantity_Purchased), 2) AS Avg_Units_Per_Transaction,\n    -- This identifies the most popular payment method in that country\n    APPROX_TOP_SUM(Payment_Method, 1, 1)[OFFSET(0)].value AS Top_Payment_Method,\n    ROUND(SUM(Profit), 2) AS Total_Profit\nFROM `project-f57ec015-00f5-4842-84d.omnisphere_retail_sales.retail_sales`\nGROUP BY Country\nORDER BY Avg_Order_Value DESC;","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"*All the SQL Queries used is attached in the dataset*","metadata":{}}]}